name: Snatch Pull
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell on the ground in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and hinge at the hips to lower into a squat position, gripping the barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and chest up as you drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As the barbell reaches hip level, explosively pull it upwards, shrugging your shoulders and pulling your elbows high and to the sides. | Step:5 As the barbell reaches its highest point, quickly drop underneath it, pulling yourself into a deep squat position. | Step:6 Catch the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended and your knees bent. | Step:7 Stand up by extending your hips and knees, keeping the barbell overhead. | Step:8 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position by reversing the movement. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Twist Row (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Take a step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Pull the v-bar towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows. | Step:7 As you pull, twist your torso to one side, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:8 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, feeling the contraction in your upper back. | Step:9 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position, untwisting your torso. | Step:10 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, alternating the twisting direction with each rep.

name: Smith Front Squat (Clean Grip)
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand facing the barbell with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Step back and position the barbell on your front shoulders, resting it on your collarbone and deltoids. | Step:5 Keep your chest up, back straight, and core engaged. | Step:6 Lower your body by bending at the knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:7 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:8 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Hack Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the barbell on the smith machine to an appropriate height for your body. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly pointed outwards. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper traps and shoulders. | Step:4 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you unrack the barbell. | Step:6 Take a step back and position your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:7 Bend your knees and lower your body down, keeping your chest up and back straight. | Step:8 Continue descending until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:9 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:10 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Low Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at a height that allows you to comfortably rest it on your upper back. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outwards. | Step:3 Step under the bar and position it across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:4 Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Unrack the bar by straightening your legs and stepping back from the rack. | Step:6 Take a deep breath and brace your core. | Step:7 Initiate the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:8 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:9 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:10 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:11 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Arm Snatch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outwards. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles, driving the barbell upwards. | Step:5 As the barbell reaches chest level, pull it upwards with your arm, keeping it close to your body. | Step:6 Rotate your elbow under the barbell and extend your arm fully overhead, locking out your elbow. | Step:7 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Power Clean
instructions: Step:1 Start with the barbell on the ground in front of you, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend down and grip the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and chest up as you lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As the barbell reaches your mid-thigh, explosively pull it upwards, shrugging your shoulders and pulling your elbows high and to the sides. | Step:5 As the barbell reaches its highest point, quickly drop underneath it, rotating your elbows around and catching the barbell on your shoulders in a front squat position. | Step:6 Stand up with the barbell, fully extending your hips and knees. | Step:7 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position, keeping control of the weight throughout the movement. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Fly (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Set up a stability ball at an incline angle. | Step:2 Attach the cable handles to the high pulleys of a cable machine. | Step:3 Sit on the stability ball facing away from the machine, with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:4 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:5 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:6 With a controlled motion, bring your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:7 Continue the motion until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:8 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat (Back Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Tricep Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with a straight bar attachment at chest height. | Step:2 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip and step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly bend your knees. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Start with your arm fully extended and perpendicular to the floor. | Step:6 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and push the bar down until your arm is fully extended. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Clean And Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell on the floor in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and hinge at the hips to lower down and grip the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Drive through your heels and extend your hips and knees to lift the barbell off the floor, keeping it close to your body. | Step:4 As the barbell reaches your thighs, explosively extend your hips, shrug your shoulders, and pull the barbell up towards your chest. | Step:5 As the barbell reaches chest height, quickly drop under it and catch it at shoulder level, with your elbows pointing forward and your palms facing up. | Step:6 From the catch position, press the barbell overhead by extending your arms and pushing the barbell straight up. | Step:7 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench facing the backrest with your chest against it. | Step:3 Grab the barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing down) and hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the barbell towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up a barbell on a squat rack at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the rack, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Lift the barbell off the rack and step back, ensuring your feet are still shoulder-width apart. | Step:6 Lower your body down into a squat, keeping your knees in line with your toes. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and exhale as you push the v-bar down until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your triceps. | Step:7 Inhale as you slowly return the v-bar to the starting position, maintaining control. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body. | Step:5 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the barbell. | Step:6 Once you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, push your hips forward and stand up straight. | Step:7 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:8 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Turkish Get Up (Squat Style)
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back with your legs extended and the kettlebell held in your right hand, arm fully extended above your shoulder. | Step:2 Bend your right knee and place your right foot flat on the ground, keeping your left leg extended. | Step:3 Pressing through your right foot, lift your hips off the ground, coming into a bridge position. | Step:4 Slide your left leg underneath your body, bending your left knee and placing your left foot flat on the ground. | Step:5 Rotate your torso to the left, bringing your left hand to the ground for support. | Step:6 Pressing through your right foot and left hand, lift your torso off the ground, coming into a kneeling position. | Step:7 From the kneeling position, stand up, keeping the kettlebell extended overhead. | Step:8 Reverse the movement to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat the exercise on the other side, starting with the kettlebell in your left hand.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Snatch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body. | Step:4 Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles, driving the dumbbell upwards in a straight line. | Step:5 As the dumbbell reaches shoulder height, quickly rotate your hand and punch it overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:6 Catch the dumbbell overhead with a slight bend in your knees and hips. | Step:7 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell Pin Presses
instructions: Step:1 Set up a barbell on a power rack at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the barbell and position yourself underneath it, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grip the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest, with your arms fully extended. | Step:5 Lower the barbell down towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in close to your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:7 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead in a straight line, fully extending your arm. | Step:4 As you press the kettlebell overhead, simultaneously dip your knees and quickly straighten them to generate momentum. | Step:5 As the kettlebell reaches its highest point, quickly drop underneath it by bending your knees and hips. | Step:6 Catch the kettlebell with a slight bend in your knees and hips, and your arm fully extended overhead. | Step:7 Stand up straight, fully extending your knees and hips, and stabilize the kettlebell overhead. | Step:8 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position by bending your knees and hips, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Straight Back High Row (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Kneel down facing the cable machine and grab the handle with one hand. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the handle towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other arm.

name: Kneeling Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your feet hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then explosively jump up into the air, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As you jump, push through your toes and fully extend your ankles, knees, and hips. | Step:5 Land softly back on the ground, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Immediately go into the next repetition, repeating the jump squat motion.

name: Cable Palm Rotational Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Step back to create tension on the cable, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your palms to face upwards as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squat Jump Step Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Explode upwards, jumping off the ground as high as you can. | Step:4 Land softly on your feet and immediately step back with one leg into a reverse lunge. | Step:5 Lower your body down until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:6 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the jump and lunge sequence on the other leg. | Step:8 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Sit on the decline bench facing the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position them at chest level. | Step:4 Keep your feet flat on the ground and your back firmly against the bench. | Step:5 Exhale and push the handles away from your body, extending your arms fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, squeezing your chest muscles. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the handles back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip and extend your arm fully. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the handle down towards your side while keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your lat muscle. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other arm.

name: Smith Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at an appropriate height for your squat. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper traps and shoulders. | Step:4 Grip the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and unrack the barbell, stepping back to clear the rack. | Step:6 Keeping your chest up and back straight, initiate the squat by bending at the hips and knees. | Step:7 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:8 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then drive through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squat Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Start with the barbell resting on your shoulders, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your chest up and your knees tracking over your toes. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the squat, explosively drive through your legs and push the barbell overhead. | Step:4 As the barbell reaches its peak, quickly drop into a split position, with one foot forward and one foot back. | Step:5 Catch the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended and your back knee slightly touching the ground. | Step:6 Stand up from the split position, bringing your feet back together. | Step:7 Lower the barbell back to your shoulders and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twisting Pull
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and step away from the machine, extending your arm fully. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart, with your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your torso to the right as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position, keeping tension on the cable. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform with your right hand.

name: Cable Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to chest height and attach the handles. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and step forward to create tension in the cables. | Step:4 Position your feet firmly on the ground and engage your core. | Step:5 Bend your elbows and bring your hands to shoulder level, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:6 Push the handles forward, extending your arms fully in front of you. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then slowly reverse the movement, bringing your hands back to shoulder level. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to chest level. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Step back and position yourself with a slight bend in your knees. | Step:5 Keep your chest up and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Lower the bar towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Double Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Bend your knees and quickly drop into a partial squat. | Step:5 Explosively extend your hips and knees, driving the kettlebells overhead. | Step:6 Lock out your arms and catch the kettlebells overhead with your knees slightly bent. | Step:7 Stand up straight and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lateral Pulldown (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to the cable machine at a high position. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the tension and allow the rope to return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown (V-Bar) (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and exhale as you push the v-bar down until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your triceps. | Step:7 Inhale as you slowly return the v-bar to the starting position, maintaining control. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twin Handle Parallel Grip Lat Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and position your thighs under the thigh pads, keeping your feet flat on the floor. | Step:4 Lean back slightly and keep your chest up, maintaining a neutral spine. | Step:5 Pull the handles down towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lats. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Judo Flip
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands at chest level, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and rotate your torso to the right, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 As you rotate, pivot your back foot and allow your hips to rotate naturally. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully and finish the movement by flipping the cable handle over your shoulder. | Step:6 Return to the starting position by reversing the movement, rotating your torso back to the center. | Step:7 Repeat the movement on the opposite side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Standing Behind Head Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height of the smith machine so that the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lift the bar off the rack and step back, maintaining a stable stance. | Step:5 Position the bar behind your head, resting on your upper traps. | Step:6 Keep your core engaged and your chest lifted throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Press the bar overhead by extending your arms, fully straightening them. | Step:8 Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upper Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat (Side Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Place a dumbbell on the floor next to the bench. | Step:3 Stand facing the bench with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Bend at the waist and place your left knee and left hand on the bench for support. | Step:5 Pick up the dumbbell with your right hand using a reverse grip (palm facing down). | Step:6 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:7 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:8 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement. | Step:9 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. | Step:10 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:11 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with your left arm.

name: Kettlebell Bottoms Up Clean From The Hang Position
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Allow the kettlebell to hang down between your legs, with your arm fully extended. | Step:4 In one fluid motion, explosively extend your hips and knees while pulling the kettlebell up towards your shoulder. | Step:5 As the kettlebell reaches shoulder height, rotate your wrist so that the bottom of the kettlebell is facing up. | Step:6 Catch the kettlebell at shoulder height with your elbow bent and your palm facing up. | Step:7 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position by reversing the movement. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Upper Chest Crossovers
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the cables at chest height. | Step:2 Stand in the center of the cable machine with one foot slightly in front of the other. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with your palms facing down and your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the cables together in front of your chest, crossing them over each other. | Step:6 Squeeze your chest muscles at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the cables back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the cables at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing away from the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Step forward slightly to create tension in the cables. | Step:5 Keep your core engaged and your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:6 With a slight bend in your elbows, slowly bring your arms forward and together in front of your chest. | Step:7 Squeeze your chest muscles at the peak of the movement. | Step:8 Slowly reverse the movement, returning your arms to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Clean-Grip Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell resting on your upper chest, with your elbows pointing forward. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, as if you are sitting back into a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your back straight as you lower down, making sure your knees do not go past your toes. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Sprint Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back with your right foot and place it on the barbell, resting the top of your foot on the bar. | Step:4 Bend your left knee and lower your body into a lunge position, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping back with your left foot. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Full Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Step under the bar and position it across your upper back, resting on your traps. | Step:4 Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Unrack the bar and take a step back, maintaining a stable stance. | Step:6 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, initiate the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:7 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as your flexibility allows. | Step:8 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then drive through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Behind Neck Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height of the smith machine so that the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lift the bar off the rack and step back, maintaining a stable stance. | Step:5 Lower the bar down to the back of your neck, keeping your elbows pointing forward. | Step:6 Press the bar up overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Squat Row (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, with your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and pull the rope towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Keep your elbows close to your body and continue pulling until your hands reach your chest. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the rope and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twisting Pull With Intensified
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and step away from the machine, extending your arm fully. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart, with your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your torso to the right as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position, keeping tension on the cable. | Step:8 (intensified variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform with your right hand.

name: Flexible Cable Triceps Pushdown (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and exhale as you push the v-bar down until your arms are fully extended. Perform with flexible intensity. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your triceps. | Step:7 Inhale as you slowly return the v-bar to the starting position, maintaining control. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump With Complex
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. Maintain complex form throughout. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pointed Cable Palm Rotational Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Step back to create tension on the cable, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent. Emphasize pointed control. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your palms to face upwards as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Judo Flip With Static
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands at chest level, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and rotate your torso to the right, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 As you rotate, pivot your back foot and allow your hips to rotate naturally. Emphasize static control. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully and finish the movement by flipping the cable handle over your shoulder. | Step:6 Return to the starting position by reversing the movement, rotating your torso back to the center. | Step:7 Repeat the movement on the opposite side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Traditional Barbell Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body. | Step:5 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the barbell. | Step:6 Once you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, push your hips forward and stand up straight. | Step:7 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:8 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on traditional movement.

name: Cable Lateral Pulldown (With Rope Attachment) Core
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to the cable machine at a high position. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Emphasize core control. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the tension and allow the rope to return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Squat Row (With Rope Attachment) Heavy
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 (heavy variation) Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, with your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and pull the rope towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Keep your elbows close to your body and continue pulling until your hands reach your chest. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the rope and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Double Alternating Hang Clean
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Allow the kettlebells to hang straight down in front of your body. | Step:4 In one fluid motion, explosively extend your hips and knees while shrugging your shoulders. | Step:5 As the kettlebells rise, pull them up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows high and out to the sides. | Step:6 Catch the kettlebells at shoulder height, with your palms facing inward and your elbows pointing forward. | Step:7 Lower the kettlebells back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stationary Bike Run
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Place your feet on the pedals and secure them with the straps if available. | Step:3 Start pedaling at a comfortable pace. | Step:4 Maintain a steady rhythm and increase the resistance as desired. | Step:5 Engage your core muscles to maintain stability and proper posture. | Step:6 Continue pedaling for the desired duration of your workout. | Step:7 Gradually decrease the resistance and slow down before coming to a complete stop. | Step:8 Stretch your legs and cool down after the workout.

name: Cable Standing Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your arm extended in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow slightly bent and your shoulder blades pulled back. | Step:4 Slowly rotate your arm outward, away from your body, while keeping your elbow in the same position. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Lift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and position it at waist height. | Step:3 Engage your core and maintain a straight back throughout the exercise. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the cable handle up towards your opposite shoulder, rotating your torso. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell Incline Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Front Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on the floor. | Step:2 Place your forearms on the ground, with your elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:3 Extend your legs straight out behind you, with your toes on the ground. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift your body off the ground, balancing on your forearms and toes. | Step:5 Keep your body in a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:6 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:7 Lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Middle Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach cables to both sides of a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand in the center of the machine with one foot slightly in front of the other. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and maintain a slight forward lean. | Step:5 Engage your chest muscles and bring your arms forward in a sweeping motion. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the center, then slowly return your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Stiff Leg Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, hinge forward at the hips, pushing your glutes back. | Step:4 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand and step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Keep your upper arm close to your body and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:5 Extend your forearm backward, straightening your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell High Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Place the barbell on your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to squat down, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kneeling Rear Delt Row (With Rope) (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low cable pulley and kneel down facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and extend your arms fully in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, pull the rope towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades. | Step:4 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement and hold for a brief pause. | Step:5 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Horizontal Pallof Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand perpendicular to the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band handle with both hands and step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Bring your hands to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body. | Step:5 Engage your core and maintain a stable stance. | Step:6 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, pushing the band away from your body. | Step:7 Hold the extended position for a few seconds, focusing on maintaining tension in your core. | Step:8 Slowly bring your hands back to your chest, resisting the pull of the band. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Alternating Narrow Grip Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footplate position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back straight and feet flat on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a narrow grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and shoulders back throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull one handle towards your torso while keeping the other handle stationary. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly return the handle to the starting position and repeat with the other side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Crossover Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the rowing machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable ropes with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the cable ropes towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Elevated Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the elevated seat facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Grab the cable rope handles with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back, maintaining a slight bend in your knees. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully contracted position. | Step:6 Slowly release the tension and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Astride Jumps (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Jump explosively upwards, extending your legs and arms. | Step:4 While in the air, spread your legs apart and bring your arms out to the sides. | Step:5 Land softly with your feet shoulder-width apart, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Twisting Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing away from you. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 As you lower the dumbbells, twist your wrists so that your palms face towards you at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then reverse the movement by pressing the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:7 As you press the dumbbells up, twist your wrists back to the starting position with palms facing away from you. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head, feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return the barbell to the starting position by reversing the motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:2 Place a barbell on the ground in front of you, centered between your feet. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, to grip the barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:4 Engage your core and drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees simultaneously. | Step:5 As you lift, keep your chest up and back straight, and push your hips forward to fully engage your glutes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Twisting Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your side facing the anchor point and grab the band with one hand. | Step:3 Step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly bend your knees. | Step:5 Bring your hand holding the band across your body, towards the opposite shoulder. | Step:6 While maintaining tension in the band, push your hand forward and away from your body, extending your arm. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other hand.

name: Cable Pulldown (Pro Lat Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your thighs are parallel to the ground and your feet are flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the lat bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and lean back slightly, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twist (Up-Down)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips and legs stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the rotation to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the high pulley of a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Engage your lats and pull the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place one foot behind you on a bench or step, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Hold onto the smith machine bar for stability. | Step:4 Bend your front knee and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Cable Overhead Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar down towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pulldown Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and slowly curl the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with one hand. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Slowly bend sideways at the waist, lowering the cable handle towards your knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulley is at the lowest position. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip and position your upper arm against the preacher bench pad. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Slowly curl your forearm towards your bicep, keeping your upper arm stationary against the pad. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your bicep. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Cable Reverse-Grip Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Using your triceps, push the bar down until your arms are fully extended and your triceps are contracted. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine and grab the handle with one hand. | Step:3 Position yourself with your back against the decline bench and your arm extended straight in front of you. | Step:4 Bend your elbow and lower the handle towards your chest while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the handle back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever One Arm Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your head up. | Step:3 Let the barbell hang in front of you with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the barbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse-Grip Straight Back Seated High Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seat facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from your hips. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the cable back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Cross-Over Revers Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to each low pulley cable and stand in the middle of the cable crossover machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a pronated grip (palms facing down) and take a step forward, positioning your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and lean forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your abs engaged. | Step:4 With your arms extended out to the sides and slightly bent at the elbows, exhale and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the cables back and upward in a reverse fly motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the handles with your palms facing forward and your arms extended straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Chest Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in front of your chest with your hands shoulder-width apart, elbows pointing forward. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball One Leg Prone Lower Body Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles to stabilize your body. | Step:4 Slowly lift one leg off the ground, keeping it straight and parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Rotate your leg outward, away from your body, while keeping your hips and upper body stable. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return your leg to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the rotation with the other leg. | Step:8 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and foot platform to your desired position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the foot platform. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, and push through your heels to lift the weight up. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and avoid rounding your shoulders. | Step:6 Extend your hips fully at the top of the movement, squeezing your glutes. | Step:7 Lower the weight back down in a controlled manner, keeping tension on your glutes and hamstrings. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Pulldown (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your thighs, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the rope back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Reverse Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide reverse grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in and your wrists straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold the cable attachment with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Pull the cable attachment straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Slowly lower the cable attachment back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Chair Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Place the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you slowly lower your body by bending your knees and hips. | Step:5 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and push the bar down until your elbows are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Low Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that the handles are at shoulder level. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and lift them off the supports, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the handles down to shoulder level, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Press the handles up overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to shoulder level. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip (On Dip-Pull-Up Cage)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the dip bars to a height that allows you to comfortably grip them. | Step:2 Stand between the bars and place your hands on each bar, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Jump up and straighten your arms, supporting your body weight on the bars. | Step:4 Bend your knees and cross your ankles behind you. | Step:5 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your chest up and your shoulders down. | Step:6 Continue lowering until your shoulders are below your elbows or until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:7 Push through your palms and extend your elbows to raise your body back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Speed Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips back and down, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Close-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squat (On Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your shoulders, gripping it with an overhand grip and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you slowly lower your body down by bending your knees, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie face up on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Sumo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at hip height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper back and shoulders. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, bending at the knees and hips. | Step:4 As you lower, push your knees out to the sides and keep your weight on your heels. | Step:5 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Decline Chest Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to a low pulley cable machine and set the bench to a decline angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your head towards the machine and grab the handle with your right hand. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:4 With a controlled motion, lower your arm out to the side until your hand is in line with your shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then reverse the motion and bring your arm back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left arm and repeat the exercise.

name: Cable Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Attach a straight bar to the cable. | Step:3 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight overhead. | Step:5 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:6 Bend your elbows and lower the bar behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:7 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Close Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Incline Press
