instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low pulley position. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench facing away from the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with one hand and bring it up to shoulder height. | Step:4 Position your feet firmly on the ground and maintain a stable position. | Step:5 Press the handle forward and upward, extending your arm fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left foot and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your right leg extended behind you for balance. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body and your left leg slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell Wide Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows slightly flared out. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rollerout From Bench
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the floor with a barbell placed on a bench in front of you. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly roll the barbell forward, extending your arms in front of you. | Step:4 Continue rolling the barbell forward until your body is fully extended and your arms are overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly roll the barbell back towards your body, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Lateral Bent-Over
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a cable machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with one hand and step back to create tension on the cable. | Step:3 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Extend your arm out to the side, parallel to the ground, with a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Smith Wide Grip Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the decline bench to the desired angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows pointed outwards. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Alternate Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the handles of the cable machine with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Position your hands at shoulder height, with your palms facing forward. | Step:3 Keep your core engaged and your back straight. | Step:4 Press one handle up and forward until your arm is fully extended. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:7 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying flat on your back on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles, then lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend at the hips and knees, lowering your torso until your back is parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders back. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift the cable handles, extending your hips and standing up straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Fixed Back Close Grip Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a fixed point above you, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy beam. | Step:2 Sit down on a bench or chair facing the band, with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:3 Grasp the band with a close grip, palms facing towards you. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the band down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lats. | Step:7 Slowly release the band back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Squatting Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to the lowest setting on a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the cable handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and knees behind your toes. | Step:5 As you squat down, curl the cable handle towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the curl, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, until your torso is almost parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge Two Legs On Bench (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start by sitting on the edge of a bench with your upper back resting against it and your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles, then press through your heels to lift your hips off the bench, creating a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your glutes. | Step:5 Slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to chest level. | Step:2 Lie flat on the bench with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:3 Grip the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the bar and lower it towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the bar touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the bar back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope One Arm Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:4 Position your upper arm against the preacher bench pad, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Slowly curl the rope handle towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:7 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the rope handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Lying Close-Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie face up on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the bar towards your chest by contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Underhand Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulldown bar is at a height above your head. | Step:2 Sit down on the seat and grab the pulldown bar with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bridge - Mountain Climber (Cross Body)
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your right foot off the ground, bringing your right knee towards your left elbow. | Step:3 Return your right foot to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left foot towards your right elbow. | Step:4 Continue alternating sides, moving at a controlled pace. | Step:5 Keep your hips level and avoid lifting your hips too high or sagging them too low. | Step:6 Maintain a steady breathing pattern throughout the exercise. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Prone Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, allowing the barbell to hang down towards the floor. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:7 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:8 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jack Burpee
secondary_muscles: quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, shoulders, triceps, core
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, placing your hands on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Kick your feet back, landing in a push-up position. | Step:4 Perform a push-up, lowering your chest to the ground and then pushing back up. | Step:5 Jump your feet forward, landing in a squat position. | Step:6 Jump up explosively, reaching your arms overhead. | Step:7 Land softly and immediately lower back into the squat position to begin the next repetition.

name: Smith Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the decline bench to the desired angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips while keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Russian Twists (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Lean back slightly while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Twist your torso to the right, bringing the cable handle towards your right hip. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the cable handle towards your left hip. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Split Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outwards. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your shoulders. | Step:3 Take a big step to the side with your right foot, keeping your left foot planted. | Step:4 Bend your right knee and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping out with your left foot. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Wide Angle Pose Sequence
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in a wide angle. | Step:2 Flex your feet and engage your quadriceps. | Step:3 Place your hands on the ground behind you for support. | Step:4 Keeping your back straight, lean forward from your hips. | Step:5 Continue leaning forward until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:6 Hold this position for a few breaths. | Step:7 Slowly release the stretch and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Delt Row (Stirrups)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a stirrup handle to a low cable pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and take a step back with your right foot, positioning your body at a slight angle. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 With your left arm extended and your palm facing down, pull the handle towards your chest by retracting your shoulder blade. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your shoulder blade. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:7 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with your right arm.

name: Barbell Wide Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and cable handles to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back straight and feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip at shoulder height. | Step:4 Push the handles forward and away from your body, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 30-45 degree incline. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back flat against the pad and feet firmly on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your upper chest, keeping your elbows slightly tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low position and attach the handles. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Hang Clean
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of your thighs. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Lower the kettlebell towards the ground, allowing it to swing between your legs. | Step:4 Quickly extend your hips and knees, using the momentum to swing the kettlebell up to shoulder height. | Step:5 As the kettlebell reaches shoulder height, rotate your wrists and catch the kettlebell in the rack position, with your elbow tucked in and the kettlebell resting on your forearm. | Step:6 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position between your legs, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to waist level. | Step:2 Stand facing the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with one hand using an overhand grip, with your palm facing down. | Step:5 Keep your elbow close to your body and pull the bar towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Standing Cross-Over High Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to each side of a cable machine at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand in the middle of the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and maintain a straight back throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your shoulder muscles and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the handles towards the front of your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulley is at the highest position. | Step:2 Sit facing the machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the cable attachment with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:5 Pull the cable attachment down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the cable back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight and chest up, and grip the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift the bar by extending your hips and knees, keeping the bar close to your body. | Step:5 Stand up straight, fully extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Lower the bar back down by bending at the hips and knees, maintaining control and keeping your back straight. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Palm Rotational Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Let your arms hang straight down, palms facing your body. | Step:4 Engage your core and pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 As you pull the dumbbells up, rotate your palms so they face away from your body. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, rotating your palms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Pushdown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean forward slightly and keep your back straight. | Step:5 Pull the bar down towards your thighs by extending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump explosively off the ground, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:4 While in mid-air, quickly bring your arms forward for balance. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next repetition. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the preacher curl pad is at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip and position your upper arm against the preacher curl pad. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Slowly curl the cable handle towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm against the pad. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Barbell Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a bench or step with a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Place one foot on the bench or step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Push through your heel and step up onto the bench or step, fully extending your hip and knee. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the top, then lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the opposite leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Guillotine Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell slowly towards your neck, keeping your elbows pointed outwards. | Step:4 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your neck. | Step:5 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated High Row (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the v-bar attachment with an overhand grip, palms facing each other, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from the hips. | Step:4 Pull the v-bar towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Forward Jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Swing your arms back for momentum. | Step:4 Jump forward explosively, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next jump. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Floor Seated Wide-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended and your back straight. | Step:2 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and position the cable machine behind you. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with a wide overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your chest lifted. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Burpee
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and placing your hands on the floor in front of you. | Step:3 Kick your feet back into a push-up position. | Step:4 Perform a push-up, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:5 Jump your feet back into the squat position. | Step:6 Jump up explosively, reaching your arms overhead. | Step:7 Land softly and immediately lower back into a squat position to begin the next repetition.

name: Incline Twisting Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:4 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the bench, curling forward. | Step:5 As you curl up, twist your torso to one side, bringing your elbow towards the opposite knee. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your torso to the other side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Bent Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and press the kettlebell overhead with your right arm, keeping your elbow locked. | Step:3 Rotate your torso to the left, shifting your weight onto your left foot. | Step:4 Bend your left knee and lower your torso towards the ground, keeping your right arm extended overhead. | Step:5 As you lower, keep your eyes on the kettlebell and your chest lifted. | Step:6 Once your left hand touches the ground, push through your left foot and straighten your left leg, driving your hips forward. | Step:7 As you drive your hips forward, use your core and right arm to press the kettlebell back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Seated Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and extend your arms straight in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged, slowly rotate your torso to one side, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the range of motion, then slowly rotate back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in front of your shoulders, resting it on your collarbone and shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:5 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Jefferson Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, resting it on the front of your body, just below your waist. | Step:3 Step your left foot forward and your right foot back, keeping your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:5 Push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement, alternating your forward and back foot with each repetition.

name: Cable Standing Row (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the v-bar attachment with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the v-bar towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated One Arm Alternate Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench facing a cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with one hand and keep your arm fully extended in front of you. | Step:3 Pull the handle towards your body, retracting your shoulder blade and keeping your elbow close to your side. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:7 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the smith machine. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the barbell up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Delt Row (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Keep your elbows slightly bent and pull the rope towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Cross-Over Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to each side of a cable machine at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand in the middle of the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and step back to create tension in the cables. | Step:4 Lean forward slightly from the hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:5 Pull the handles down and across your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Low Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the handles to the low pulleys of a cable machine and select an appropriate weight. | Step:2 Stand in the middle of the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Maintaining control, slowly bring your arms forward in a sweeping motion, crossing them in front of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, feeling the stretch in your chest muscles. | Step:6 Reverse the motion and slowly return your arms to the starting position, keeping tension on your chest muscles throughout. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your hamstrings and glutes to lift the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Zercher Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in the crooks of your elbows, with your hands gripping the bar for stability. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you lower your hips back and down into a squat position. | Step:4 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a 45-degree incline. | Step:2 Attach the cable handles to the high pulleys. | Step:3 Sit on the bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:4 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and bring them to shoulder height. | Step:5 Push the handles forward and upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pushdown (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to a high pulley on a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Exhale and push the rope downward by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position by allowing your elbows to flex. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the handles are at shoulder height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and bring them up to shoulder level, with your elbows bent and pointing outwards. | Step:4 Press the handles upwards until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Wide-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with a wide overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from the hips. | Step:4 Pull the handle towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly twist your torso to one side, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly rotate back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the twist to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Skullcrusher
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a reverse grip, palms facing towards your face, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping your elbows in and your wrists straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell on the ground in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and hinge at the hips to lower your torso and grip the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and chest lifted as you drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As you stand up straight, squeeze your glutes and keep your core engaged. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the ground by bending at the hips and knees, keeping your back straight. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Fixed Back Underhand Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point above your head. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Step back to create tension in the band, keeping your arms fully extended. | Step:5 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pull the band down towards your chest, leading with your elbows. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lats. | Step:8 Slowly release the tension in the band and return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Hammer Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope attachment to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). | Step:4 Position your upper arms against the preacher bench pad, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the rope towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps. | Step:6 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly lower the rope back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Zercher Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in the crooks of your elbows, with your hands gripping the barbell for stability. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you lower your hips back and down into a squat position. | Step:4 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:5 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Floor Fly (With Barbell)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell until your arms are parallel to the floor, feeling a stretch in your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bent Knee Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to raise your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Standing Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and bring it down to shoulder level, with your palms facing forward. | Step:4 Press the barbell upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Full Range Of Motion
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the lat pulldown machine with your knees positioned under the pads. | Step:2 Grasp the cable bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lean back slightly and keep your chest up, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Wide Grip Rear Pulldown Behind Neck
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the pulldown bar is at a height above your head. | Step:2 Sit down on the seat and grab the pulldown bar with a wide overhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your chest up as you lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Thibaudeau Kayak Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and sit facing the machine with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your right hand and extend your arm fully, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:3 Lean forward from your hips, keeping your back straight and your abs engaged. | Step:4 Pull the handle towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blade and bending your elbow, keeping your arm close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform with your left arm.

name: Rope Climb
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the rope with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grab the rope with both hands, palms facing towards you. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:4 Begin pulling yourself up the rope by alternating hand-over-hand movements. | Step:5 Use your legs to assist in the upward movement. | Step:6 Continue climbing until you reach the desired height or the top of the rope. | Step:7 To descend, reverse the hand-over-hand movement while controlling your descent. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Machine Decline Close Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench on the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell is just above your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse Grip Triceps Pushdown (Sz-Bar) (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and slowly push the bar down until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Toe Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine bar to a height that allows you to comfortably stand with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Position yourself under the bar with your shoulders directly below it and your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Place the balls of your feet on a raised platform or weight plates, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Burpee
secondary_muscles: quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, shoulders, triceps, core
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, placing the dumbbells on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Kick your feet back into a push-up position, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Perform a push-up, bending your elbows and lowering your chest towards the ground. | Step:5 Jump your feet back towards your hands, landing in a squat position. | Step:6 Stand up explosively, lifting the dumbbells off the ground and bringing them to your shoulders. | Step:7 Press the dumbbells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Lower the dumbbells back to your shoulders and repeat the entire sequence for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Arm Side Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and lower the barbell towards the outside of your leg, keeping your arm straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Lower the barbell as far as you can while maintaining good form. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Smith Wide Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the bench to a comfortable position on the smith machine. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows out to the sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pendlay Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and twist your torso to the right, pulling the cable across your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, feeling the contraction in your abs and obliques. | Step:5 Slowly return to the starting position, resisting the cable's pull. | Step:6 Repeat the movement to the left side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Hack Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell behind your legs, resting it on your upper thighs. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending at the knees and hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the smith machine to a comfortable incline angle. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip that is slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the bar and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the bar is just above your chest. | Step:6 Push the bar back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lateral Pulldown With V-Bar
instructions: Step:1 Sit down on the cable pulldown machine and grab the v-bar attachment with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Adjust the knee pad so that your thighs are secured under it. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean back slightly. | Step:4 Pull the v-bar down towards your upper chest while keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your back muscles at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly return the v-bar to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Lying Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable weight. | Step:2 Lie on your back on the sled machine with your feet on the footplate. | Step:3 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly angled outwards. | Step:4 Grip the handles of the sled machine for stability. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:6 Push through your heels and extend your legs to lift the sled. | Step:7 Lower the sled back down by bending your knees and hips. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Behind Head Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and bring it down to shoulder level, behind your head. | Step:4 Press the barbell upward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Side Bent V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Slowly bend your torso to the right side, lowering the barbell towards your right knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement on the left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Shoulder Internal Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your arm extended straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow slightly bent and your shoulder blades pulled back and down. | Step:4 Slowly rotate your arm inward, bringing the cable handle towards the center of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Decline Seated Wide-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the decline bench facing the cable machine with your feet securely placed on the footrests. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with a wide overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the cable back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a cable handle in one hand and position your arm at chest height, elbow bent. | Step:3 Place your other hand on your hip for stability. | Step:4 Press the cable handle forward, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Hip Adduction
instructions: Step:1 Attach the ankle cuff to your ankle and stand facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Position yourself far enough away from the machine so that there is tension on the cable. | Step:3 Place your hands on the machine for support. | Step:4 Keeping your leg straight, slowly move your leg across your body towards the midline. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Hammer Curl And Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your back straight. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the dumbbell in your right hand towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the curl with your left hand. | Step:7 After completing the curl with your left hand, exhale and press the dumbbell in your right hand overhead. | Step:8 Extend your arm fully and hold for a moment at the top. | Step:9 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:10 Repeat the press with your left hand. | Step:11 Continue alternating between curls and presses for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Close Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable High Row (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Kneel down in front of the cable machine and grab the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit back on your heels, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the bar towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Bar Lateral Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable pulley to a high position and attach a straight bar. | Step:2 Sit facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back slightly and keep your chest up, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:5 Pull the bar down towards your chest, leading with your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Drop Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump up explosively, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:4 While in mid-air, quickly bring your feet together. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately drop back into a squat position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Narrow Stance Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you slowly lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Decline Reverse-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with one hand, palm facing inward, and extend your arm fully. | Step:4 Pull the cable handle towards your body, keeping your elbow close to your side, until your hand reaches your lower chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly extend your arm back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Smith Machine Reverse Decline Close Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in front of your chest with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Slowly twist your torso to the right, pivoting on your feet and hips, while keeping your lower body stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the twist to the left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet on the footrests. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a cable handle in one hand and extend your arm out to the side, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow slightly bent and your palm facing forward. | Step:4 Slowly bring your arm across your body, squeezing your chest muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Cross-Over Variation
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable pulleys to chest height. | Step:2 Stand in the center of the cable machine with one foot in front of the other. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with your palms facing down and your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:4 Take a step forward, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:5 With a slight bend in your elbows, bring your hands together in front of your chest. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then slowly return your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Take a large step forward with one leg, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, while keeping your back leg straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Pike-To-Cobra Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, forming an inverted V shape with your body. | Step:3 Lower your upper body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 As you lower down, shift your weight forward and transition into a cobra pose by straightening your arms and lifting your chest up. | Step:5 Reverse the movement by bending your elbows and lowering your chest back down towards the ground. | Step:6 Push through your hands to return to the inverted V position. | Step:7 Continue the movement by lowering your hips back down towards the ground, returning to the starting push-up position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and bring it to shoulder level, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:4 Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the bar off the rack and position it at shoulder level, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:4 Press the bar upward until your arms are fully extended overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to shoulder level. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pushdown (Straight Arm) V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you exhale and push the bar down towards your thighs. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position while inhaling. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Bench Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and attach a cable handle to the low pulley. | Step:2 Sit on the bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip and extend your arms fully in front of you. | Step:4 Lean forward from your hips while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the cable handle towards your chest by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Arm Pulldown (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully in front of you, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Engage your lats and slowly pull the rope down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Narrow Grip Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to ensure proper form. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a narrow grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your torso, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Box Jump Down With One Leg Stabilization
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a box or platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and jump onto the box, landing softly with one foot on the box and the other foot hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Stabilize yourself on the box with the foot that is on it, while keeping the other foot off the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, engaging your calf muscles to maintain balance. | Step:5 Slowly step down with the foot that is on the box, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the exercise with the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Clean
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your hips into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Explosively extend your hips and knees, driving through your heels to jump off the ground. | Step:4 As you jump, shrug your shoulders and pull the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping them close to your body. | Step:5 Catch the dumbbells at shoulder height, with your elbows pointing forward and your palms facing up. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position by reversing the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Hang Clean
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Allow the kettlebells to hang in front of your body with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 In one fluid motion, explosively extend your hips, shrug your shoulders, and pull the kettlebells up towards your shoulders. | Step:5 As the kettlebells reach shoulder height, rotate your wrists and catch the kettlebells in the rack position, with your palms facing inward and the kettlebells resting on the outside of your forearms. | Step:6 Lower the kettlebells back down to the starting position and repeat the movement with the opposite arm. | Step:7 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Advanced Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in your right hand, with your arm extended overhead and your palm facing forward. | Step:3 Rotate your left foot slightly to the right, and shift your weight onto your left leg. | Step:4 Bend your left knee and hinge at the hip, lowering your torso towards the left side. | Step:5 Keep your right arm extended overhead and your eyes on the kettlebell. | Step:6 As you lower your torso, allow your right leg to straighten and your right foot to pivot slightly. | Step:7 Lower your torso until you feel a stretch in your left hamstring and your right arm is pointing towards the ground. | Step:8 Pause for a moment, then engage your core and push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable pulldown machine so that the seat is at a comfortable height and the knee pad is secured. | Step:2 Sit on the seat with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the cable bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back slightly and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the cable bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the rowing machine with your feet flat on the footrests and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable ropes with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pull the cable ropes towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Back Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from the hips. | Step:4 Pull the cable handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat and footplate of the smith machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Push the footplate away from you by extending your legs, keeping your back against the backrest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position. | Step:6 Slowly bend your knees and lower the footplate back towards you, returning to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Machine Bicep Curl
